WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good morning, Jacob. It's Monday, March thirtieth, twenty twenty-six. Six

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
A-M in Jefferson City, eighty-seven degrees on the way, and

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
I hope you're sitting down because we have a lot

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
to get through. Let's start with your day. Ben arrives

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
today to help with the carpet install, which happens tomorrow

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
morning at nine. Payday is also tomorrow. It's eighty-seven and

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
sunny in Jeff City, which means your condo is going

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
to be a sauna for the carpet guys. Sixty-four tonight.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
Over in Tacoma, Katelyn gets a rare sunny day at

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
forty-nine degrees. Spring is arriving in the Pacific Northwest about

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
six weeks behind Missouri's aggressive schedule. Your week is loaded.

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
Wednesday: Apple turns fifty, Q-two starts, and Karen announces her

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
retirement at eleven A-M. Thursday is the big one. Anthropic

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
pilot discussion at nine A-M, Bill Review Training at two

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
P-M, dinner with Alex, Chris, and Dustin at six, and

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
the government's appeal deadline on Judge Lin's Anthropic ruling. That's

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
four major events in one day. Now for your texts.

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
Katelyn was up late last night. She took Risotto to

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
a dog park, debated whether that bird was a turkey

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
vulture or an eagle, continued developing the crow feeder's formal

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
doctrine — commandment two is apparently "couches are for dogs,

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
people should sit on the floor" — and made chili

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
for meal prep but forgot the seasoning packet. Update as

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
of midnight: it turned out fine. Quote, "maybe a little

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
less flavorful but decent." The seasoning crisis has been resolved.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
Dustin dropped some big news. He's going to Europe for

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
the first time. May eighth through the twenty-first. Five countries

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
in thirteen days: Amsterdam, Brussels, Ghent, Paris, Berlin, Lagos Portugal,

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
Faro, and Rome. He's joining someone for the last two

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
weeks of their trip and he's, quote, "extremely excited." He

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
also ordered the AirPods Max two in Midnight Black. Alex

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
corrected everyone that there is no black in Apple's vocabulary,

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
only Midnight. This is apparently a hill worth dying on.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
Alex hinted at needing to buy all of Apple's new

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
home stuff this year. Something's going on with someone named

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
Shayla, and when Jacob asked, Alex deflected with "why do

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
you know anything?" and then "Dustin?" — suggesting Dustin may

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
have spilled something he shouldn't have. Chris Hornsey sent a

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
small-town traffic report meme: "Well Greg, westbound on West Main,

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
we got a little church traffic backing up the road

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
almost to the cemetery." He then apologized for the joke

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
since none of you grew up in a major metro

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
area. Peak Chris energy. Now, the news. Here's what's happening

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
locally first. The D-H-S shutdown is on day forty-five, but

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
T-S-A workers should start seeing paychecks today. Trump signed a

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
presidential memorandum redirecting funds. The legal authority is contested, but

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
the money is moving. Five hundred officers have quit permanently.

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
Congress is still on recess. On to the quick status

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
board. The Iran war is on day thirty-one. Trump told

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
the Financial Times he might, quote, "take the oil" and

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
seize Kharg Island. The Wall Street Journal reports he's considering

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
a military operation to grab a thousand pounds of enriched

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
uranium. There are now fifty thousand U-S troops in the

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
Middle East. Brent crude hit one-sixteen. The coal industry is

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
surging — Australian miner Yancoal is up forty percent since

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
the war started. Japan and South Korea are reactivating old

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
coal plants. G-seven ministers are holding emergency talks today. Pakistan

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
has emerged as a surprise mediator, hosting Egyptian, Saudi, and

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
Turkish foreign ministers for peace talks. Thirteen U-S service members

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
have been killed and nearly three hundred wounded since February

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
twenty-eighth. The Anthropic versus Pentagon case: Judge Lin's injunction holds.

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
The government has until Thursday to appeal to the Ninth

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
Circuit. That's the same day as your pilot meeting. If

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
they don't appeal, Anthropic's government business normalizes. All three watchlist

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
roles are still posted: Anthropic Institute Analyst, Communications Manager, and

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
Geopolitics Analyst. Now for the deep dives. The biggest business

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
story today is SpaceX preparing the largest I-P-O in history.

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
Seventy-five billion dollars at a one-point-seven-five trillion dollar valuation. That's

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
more than the entire U-S I-P-O market raised in twenty

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
twenty-four and twenty twenty-five combined. Musk recently merged X-A-I into

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
SpaceX, all eleven X-A-I co-founders have left, and the unit

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:48.000
is hemorrhaging money. But Polymarket gives it an eighty-nine-point-five percent

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
chance of being the biggest I-P-O of the year. In

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.000
tech and A-I news: Anthropic's Claude Mythos leak continues to

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
reverberate. Axios reports the company is privately warning government officials

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
that the model, quote, "presages an upcoming wave of models

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
that can exploit vulnerabilities in ways that far outpace the

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
efforts of defenders." Cybersecurity stocks remain depressed. The New Stack

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
called March twenty twenty-six "Anthropic's madcap March: fourteen-plus launches, five

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
outages, and an accidental leak." The F-T-C chairman compared media

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
companies demanding payment for A-I training data to "rent-seeking" and

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.000
"collecting tolls." This is the Trump administration giving A-I companies

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
a green light to train on news content. Billions are

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:36.000
at stake in the New York Times and News Corp

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:40.000
lawsuits. N-A-S-A's Artemis crew entered quarantine ahead of a potential

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.000
Wednesday launch — the first crewed trip around the moon

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.000
since nineteen seventy-two. They've expanded plans to include a permanent

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.000
moon base within seven years. For jobs, the City of

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:56.000
Seattle Economics and Revenue Analyst is now on day thirteen.

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
Government postings typically close at fourteen to twenty-one days. If

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.000
you're applying, this is your last window. A new Senior

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:08.000
Budget Analyst role at Seattle Colleges popped up — lower

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.000
salary but squarely in your wheelhouse. March Madness update: UConn

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.000
pulled off a nineteen-point comeback against number-one Duke. Braylon Mullins

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:20.000
hit a game-winning three with zero-point-four seconds left. The Final

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.000
Four is Saturday: UConn versus Illinois, Michigan versus Arizona. And

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.000
here's the close. Elon Musk decided that running Tesla, SpaceX,

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:32.000
X, X-A-I, and the federal government's efficiency department wasn't enough,

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:36.000
so he merged three of them into one company and

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:40.000
is now selling it for one-point-seven-five trillion dollars. Which is

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:44.000
the financial equivalent of dumping all your leftovers into one

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:48.000
Tupperware and calling it a casserole. Trump says he might

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:52.000
take Iran's oil, the coal industry is having its comeback

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:56.000
tour, N-A-S-A is going to the moon, and Dustin is

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:00.000
going to Europe for the first time — visiting five

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:04.000
countries in thirteen days with someone he hasn't seen since

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:08.000
January. Katelyn made chili without seasoning and it turned out

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:12.000
"fine," which is the culinary equivalent of "it's not you,

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:16.000
it's me." Ben arrives today. Carpet tomorrow. Payday tomorrow. Pilot

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:20.000
meeting Thursday. And somewhere in a Ninth Circuit clerk's office,

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:24.000
a government attorney is deciding whether to appeal an injunction

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:28.000
on the same day you'll be making the case for

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:32.000
Claude at your own workplace. Happy Monday, Jacob. It's eighty-seven

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:32.800
degrees. Hydrate.
